      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ACHY BREAKY ARK (10) was a big improver last time out when he led to score by 2.6 metres at Wagga. A back row draw poses more of a challenge but he has recorded a win and a placing in two previous third-up attempts and won the only time he raced here so has strong claims with even luck. TULHURST TIMMY (2) scored at Bathurst two runs ago before a brave effort for second at his latest appearance at this circuit and distance, coming from the back row to be beaten a head. Should enjoy an economical run from this draw so could put himself back into the winners' stall. WHYKIKAMOOCOW (1) has been coming from wider or second row barriers and while down the track last time he scored back-to-back wins here prior. Should get his chance from the ace draw. MARY ANNE ROSE (12) was held up in a last-start fourth and placed at Redcliffe prior. Can feature with even luck.",
